width=\"16\"></a> - A privacy-respecting mobile app that allows you to keep track of your own location.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T11:32:42.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kLhoRyLxwAE\">Modern Web UI with Blazor WebAssembly</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-56%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> June 11, 2020 - Modern Web UI with Blazor WebAssembly by <a href=\"https://ndcoslo.com/speaker/steve-sanderson/\">Steve Sanderson at the NDC Oslo 2020</a>. Client-side web development has long been the sole domain of JavaScript. WebAssembly is changing that by opening up the web to the full ecosystem of languages, frameworks, and tools. ASP.NET Blazor is all about building modern web applications be that on the server or the client. In this session I'll show you how to build beautiful and interactive client-side web UI, all with C# instead of JavaScript.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:55:32.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Sample Projects</h2><h3>Games</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/bjorndaniel/Blazorships\">Blazorships</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/bjorndaniel/Blazorships\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">8</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":8,\"repo\":\"bjorndaniel/Blazorships\"}____TRACK_AWESOM