TEM_END--> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/github/stars/klemmchr/MvvmBlazor?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=604800\" alt=\"stars\"> <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/github/last-commit/klemmchr/MvvmBlazor?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=86400\" alt=\"last commit\"> BlazorMVVM is a small framework for building Blazor and BlazorServerside apps. With it's simple to use MVVM pattern you can boost up your development speed while minimizing the hazzle to just make it work.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:50:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.twitch.tv/videos/717583951\">Blazor Game Client + Working on GUI System</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-205%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=twitch\" alt=\"duration\"> August 23, 2020 - Blazor Game Client + Working on GUI System.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:50:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=I74hkInjziM&#x26;feature=youtu.be\">How to Create Services in Client Side Apps</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-17%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> August 21, 2020 - We are upgrading our Blazor App Tour Of Heroes with Services! This will allow the components to keep state even when we navigate away along with creating some reusable code for our apis. If you like this video please subscribe and let me know you would like to see more. Based of Tour of Heroes section 4.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:50:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vdvIz5QxFFU\">Write OnClick Events in C# using Blazor and Eliminate JavaScript</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-14%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> August 25, 2020 - JavaScript can be eliminated for implementing an OnClick event and many other HTML event attributes. With Blazor, we go ahead and write an OnClick event in C# without the need for JavaScript.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:41:45.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VaX73p3JfV4&#x26;feature=youtu.be\">Blazor Train: Data Access</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-33%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> August 24, 2020 - Carl brings together an API layer, a generic data manager, and EF Core to create a complete solution.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:41:45.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=12XAjpuwByo\">The .NET Docs Show - .NET open-source projects</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-65%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> August 24, 2020 - Chat with Isaac Levin (@isaacrlevin) about some exciting .NET open source projects he's been working on. By <a href=\"https://dotnetdocs.dev/\">The .NET Docs show</a>. Article on <a href=\"https://dev.to/dotnet/the-net-docs-show-open-source-net-projects-2h39\">Dev.to</a> about this episode.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:41:45.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://dev.to/dotnet/the-net-docs-show-open-source-net-projects-2h39\">The .NET Docs Show: Open source .NET projects</a> - August 24, 2020 - In this episode of The .NET Docs Show, Isaac Levin (@isaacrlevin) discusses several of his open source .NET projects. As part of this week's #CheckUp, we share an MS Learn module for building with Microsoft Graph as it related to the PresenceLight project. <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=12XAjpuwByo\">Video on YouTube</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:41:45.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.telerik.com/blogs/how-to-work-with-client-side-blazor\">How to Work With Client-Side Blazor</a> - August 20, 2020 - You’ve probably heard talk of Blazor Wasm, but what is it and how can you use it to rapidly build your web applications?</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:41:45.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://visualstudiomagazine.com/articles/2020/08/11/blazor-tooling-updates.aspx\">What's New in Blazor Tooling Updates</a> - August 11, 2020 - What's New in Blazor Tooling Updates, on Visual Studio Magazine.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:41:45.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://visualstudiomagazine.com/articles/2020/08/03/blazor-pwa.aspx\">Creating a Progressive Web App with Blazor WebAssembly</a> - August 3, 2020 - Not surprisingly, it's dead easy to create an app in Blazor that runs outside of the browser window and (potentially) in an offline mode. Before you get carried away, though, there are some key design decisions to make, by Visual Studio Magazine.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:41:45.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Career</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://jacobian.org/2019/apr/23/questions-for-employers-director-vp/\">My questions for prospective employers (Director/VP roles)</a> - Be prepared to ask them as a recruiter or being asked about them for senior management roles.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:13:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Career</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>“Since managers are not tied to a sector (in the way nurses or musicians are), the good ones tend to go where they are payed good money and the bad ones end up wreaking havoc where they are payed at least some money. That, also, is <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baumol%27s_cost_disease\">Baumol</a> in action.” (<a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=20448929\">source</a>) - Explains how the pool of professional managers gets distributed into the various sectors of the economy.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:13:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Career</h2><h3>Promotion</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://workplace.stackexchange.com/questions/145709/how-to-discipline-overeager-engineer\">How to discipline overeager engineer</a> - Over-achieving talent is looking for a management promotion. Management does not recognize effort. Engineer become disgruntled and management is looking to discipline him. A case-study of a bad situation in which both side shows clumsiness.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:13:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Career</h2><h3>Promotion</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>“Most people realize by their 30s that prestige is a sucker's game” (<a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=11833832\">source</a>) - So not chase promotion for the title only.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:13:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Career</h2><h3>Performance Reviews</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.joelonsoftware.com/2000/04/03/incentive-pay-considered-harmful/\">Incentive Pay Considered Harmful</a> - “Incentives (or bribes) simply can't work in the workplace. (…) Most software managers have no choice but to go along with performance review systems that are already in place. If you're in this position, the only way to prevent teamicide is to simply give everyone on your team a gushing review”.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:13:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Career</h2><h3>Performance Reviews</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>“If anything in your performance review is a surprise, then I have failed as a manager.” (<a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=17249767\">source</a>).</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:13:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Career</h2><h3>Performance Reviews</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>“This is what I loved about working at Netflix. We didn't have performance reviews. It was assumed that your performance was good to excellent, otherwise you wouldn't be working there anymore. You had a constant feedback loop with your manager on performance, but nothing was ever formal.” (<a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=23861960\">source</a>).</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:13:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Career</h2><h3>Performance Reviews</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>“The system a software developer works in shapes their performance so much more than individual differences.” (<a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=21972033\">source</a>).</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:13:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"vlang/awesome-v","categoryHTML":"<h2>Applications</h2><h3>Web</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/scurty-labs/vblog\">vblog</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/scurty-labs/vblog\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-b